    "description": "An ancient place, located in modern Syria, with remains of an ancient basilica. Inscribed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2011 as part of the \"Ancient Villages of Northern Syria.\"",
    "details": "<div>\r\n<p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1348/\">Inscribed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site</a> in 2011 as part of the \"Ancient Villages of Northern Syria\" under criteria iii, iv, and v of UNESCO's World Heritage List <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://whc.unesco.org/en/criteria/\">Operational Guidelines</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Specific archaeological components include:</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Qalb Loze Basilica</strong>, which probably dates to the end of the 5th century.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The Basilica is located within an equally well-preserved enclosure in the heart of a village that was re-occupied from the 10th century AD. The village includes areas with <strong>paved roof</strong>, <strong>terraces</strong>, and <strong>monumental entrances</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>",
